Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.07,0:00:03.77,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:05.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:06.69,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.44,0:00:09.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A parent is a parent, but a child is different!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:10.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran's challenge outdoes Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:12.59,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.59,0:00:13.99,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.48,0:00:15.99,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.85,0:02:04.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:08.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Akasaka Princess Hotel's a\Nnice hotel, but this hill's a killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:09.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.95,0:02:12.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge right away and\Njump right into the pool, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.36,0:02:13.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.88,0:02:17.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna catch me a hot guy,\Nso don't get in my way, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.78,0:02:19.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.38,0:02:24.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, have you heard\Nanything from Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:26.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not a word since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:29.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he working on another case?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:33.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't understand how anyone\Ncan get so worked up over a case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.12,0:02:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that car...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.60,0:02:39.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't look good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:45.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.78,0:02:50.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry! Are you two all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.42,0:02:52.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.80,0:02:54.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just barely...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.21,0:02:57.55,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka Princess Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:03:01.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Yoshino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're an\Ninstructor at a flower design school?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:05.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I commute to Shizuoka five days a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:07.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuoka? That's pretty far, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.97,0:03:13.52,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie Yoshino (31)\NFlower Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:14.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I was just on my way to school\Nwhen I remembered today was a holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.60,0:03:19.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I called my husband—\Nhe works for an insurance company—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.81,0:03:23.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and we made plans to meet here at this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to have lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.21,0:03:27.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.13,0:03:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry about what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.55,0:03:32.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got dizzy all of a sudden\Nand blacked out for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.81,0:03:36.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been getting dizzy spells and\Nsplitting headaches a lot lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:42.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... The doctor couldn't find anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:49.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably the weather. The\Ntemperature's been all over the place lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.55,0:03:52.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I guess the fatigue's been building up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:54.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,since I have to drive to and\Nfrom Shizuoka every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, when there's no school,\Nor when it's cool, even on a weekday,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.01,0:04:00.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel fine—nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.14,0:04:02.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.59,0:04:03.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.92,0:04:06.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:09.24,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Akio Yoshino (33)\NInsurance Agent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.74,0:04:09.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my husband, Akio Yoshino.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.25,0:04:10.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.49,0:04:14.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ran Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Sonoko Suzuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.32,0:04:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had another dizzy spell and nearly ran them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.58,0:04:20.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.02,0:04:21.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you two hurt at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:24.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're fine. But it was a close call.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.90,0:04:27.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your wife was nice enough to treat us to lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.56,0:04:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.99,0:04:31.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please accept my apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:32.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:36.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I rested for a bit, so now I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.89,0:04:39.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... I'm so relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:41.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:44.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, I think we'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, you were going\Nto the pool, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:49.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:51.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you two live?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In Beika Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:58.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's not far from us. I live in Haido Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:05:00.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We live right near the park.\NPlease drop by sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.93,0:05:01.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.61,0:05:05.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bump...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.97,0:05:11.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:15.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, watch your step! There's a bump here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.55,0:05:27.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:30.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:37.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he knew Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just had a dizzy spell, so why didn't he warn her about the bump?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.64,0:05:40.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She could've gotten badly hurt\Nif she tripped and fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.90,0:05:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see why you're making\Nsuch a big deal out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:49.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sonoko warned me about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:51.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I know {\i1}he{\i0} would have too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:54.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:05:58.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.82,0:06:02.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm worried about that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:04.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll go over to visit\NChie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and check things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.81,0:06:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:10.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to find out what's causing her to\Nhave those headaches and dizzy spells!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:12.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:14.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not a doctor. Don't stick your\Nneck out where it doesn't belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:17.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not stupid, I can figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:18.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh, do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.67,0:06:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I most certainly will!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:26.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran's not usually like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.55,0:06:29.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But she has a point. Something's fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:32.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can I go with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:35.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to come along, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:37.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll ask Sonoko to come along,\Nand we'll all go together!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.97,0:06:40.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:43.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll have my rice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:44.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:48.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a grouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.57,0:06:52.03,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshino Residence
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:55.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This place is super-nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.40,0:06:58.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The garden's so well cared-for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:00.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your home's so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.45,0:07:02.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.80,0:07:05.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We just finished building this\Nplace a month and a half ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a feeling it was new.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:11.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A new house, how wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:15.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But dealing with a ¥40,000,000 loan's pretty rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.27,0:07:20.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we both have to work,\Nor we'd never make ends meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:23.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:23.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.65,0:07:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for barging in on you on your day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.86,0:07:30.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.02,0:07:32.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, my husband went out\Nthis morning, so I'm alone today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.40,0:07:35.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband seems so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:37.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:39.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He loves cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.43,0:07:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's been complaining lately that he hasn't\Nbeen able to go out for drives like he used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:47.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's why he goes out walking\Nevery morning, to take his mind off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:51.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And while he's out, I fix breakfast.\NThat's our daily routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.19,0:07:53.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.66,0:07:56.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This may be a strange thing to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:07:58.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but why do you go all the way\Nto Shizuoka to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:01.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To help pay for the loan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:05.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to teach at a design school here in the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.87,0:08:09.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but my husband told me\Nabout this school in Shizuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:12.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The pay was better there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.40,0:08:15.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.29,0:08:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, isn't driving there every day pretty hard on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.83,0:08:21.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.16,0:08:23.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you took the train, you'd at\Nleast be able to get some sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:27.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I enjoy driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.57,0:08:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The entrance to the expressway is nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.53,0:08:33.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's much more convenient when you have a\Nlot of supplies and large equipment, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.45,0:08:34.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.50,0:08:38.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, have you ever though about insur—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.25,0:08:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:41.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot, you're still in high school!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.66,0:08:42.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:44.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.26,0:08:46.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband works for an insurance company,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.76,0:08:49.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've gotten into the habit of\Nsuggesting people get insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.74,0:08:52.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so you're giving your husband a hand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.70,0:08:54.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:09:00.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt bad about suggesting it to others, so I just recently raised my policy to ¥100,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.24,0:09:02.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,¥100,000,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.78,0:09:06.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband asked me to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:09.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The monthly payments are very high,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.10,0:09:10.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's the kind of policy where\Nafter the fixed period has passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.85,0:09:13.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even if you cancel the policy,\Nyou still get the premium back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.71,0:09:16.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured it would make his\Njob performance look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.15,0:09:18.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, you're really crazy about him, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:20.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.47,0:09:24.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}¥100,000,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:25.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.55,0:09:26.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.95,0:09:32.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but when did you start\Nhaving those headaches and dizzy spells?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:37.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About a month ago, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.62,0:09:38.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A month ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.81,0:09:42.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Half a month after the house was built...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's what they call\N"sick house syndrome"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.84,0:09:51.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sick house syndrome...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{What? Shikuhakku?}What? "Sick hack"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.34,0:09:58.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I said "sick house syndrome"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.13,0:10:00.93,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Sick House Syndrome
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:02.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's when people get sick from the fumes given off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from the lumber and paint used to build a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:10.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, I'm sure even\Nyou've heard of formaldehyde...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:10.65,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Formaldehyde
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(262,336,0,236)}F
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(274,336,0,400)}o
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(283,336,283,500)}r
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(295,336,320,500)}m
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(310,336,350,500)}a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(317,336,480,500)}l
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(326,336,650,500)}d
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(336,336,650,336)}e
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(346,336,650,300)}h
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(356,336,650,200)}y
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(367,336,650,100)}d
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:10.86,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,100)\bord0\shad0\move(377,336,377,0)}e
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.00,0:10:12.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take me for an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.20,0:10:14.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.95,0:10:17.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure. But I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.95,0:10:19.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.60,0:10:23.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The contractor who built this\Nhouse is a friend of my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.07,0:10:30.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband would have told them not\Nto use anything that was dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:35.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still think you should have it checked out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:38.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The contractor could've deceived you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.25,0:10:39.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.14,0:10:42.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know of any companies that specialize\Nin checking for contaminated building supplies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad might know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:49.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right then, let's ask him right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.36,0:10:52.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I think you should have it\Nchecked, just to be on the safe side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:54.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.63,0:11:06.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, you've been acting strange today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.59,0:11:08.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you insist on getting her house checked?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.79,0:11:11.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had my reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:15.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} thinks Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband Akio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.28,0:11:20.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is trying to kill her to collect\Non her insurance policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.65,0:11:22.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:24.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:28.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:35.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Akio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} gets the contractor to build\Nthe house using dangerous materials,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:38.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so that Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} starts to become ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he suggests she take the job\Nat the design school in Shizuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:47.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:53.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} does as he suggests, and drives to and from work on the expressway every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.65,0:11:55.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If she were to have a dizzy spell while driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:08.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.40,0:12:10.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're overthinking this, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, wouldn't the house\Nmake Akio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sick too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.75,0:12:18.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He lives there too, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:23.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But those materials could've been used\Nonly for her room and the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.62,0:12:29.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we have no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:33.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But as long as the possibility exists,\NI thought it was best to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:41.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At this point, we still don't know\Nif Ran's suspicions are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:45.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But something wasn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.55,0:12:47.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I couldn't put my finger on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.23,0:12:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a device that measures\Nthe amount of formaldehyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:56.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility that different\Nmaterials were used in each room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:13:00.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I think it's best if we\Nchecked every room to be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:03.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:05.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right then, let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.64,0:13:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Chie told me about this, I was shaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.33,0:13:15.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, there is a possibility the\Ncontractor did use those kind of materials,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.78,0:13:19.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I figured it might be best\Nto have the kitchen checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.27,0:13:26.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.10,0:13:28.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pick up some cake on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.90,0:13:30.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.22,0:13:31.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:37.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He really loves to take walks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to take a walk too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:43.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Don't stay out too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:43.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.38,0:14:19.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That customer's going to buy it, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:22.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He used to come in\Nall the time on his days off,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:23.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I think he's made up his mind now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.38,0:14:28.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}¥25,000,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.44,0:14:30.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh geez, is he serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.74,0:14:32.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have the results!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:36.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Every room shows a level much\Nlower than 0.08 parts per million,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.82,0:14:41.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which is the level the Ministry of Health\Nand Welfare declared safe four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.25,0:14:44.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.60,0:14:45.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:49.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It means this house is absolutely safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:50.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.92,0:14:56.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not "sick house\Nsyndrome" that's making me sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:57.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:15:00.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try to get to bed earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:01.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.18,0:15:08.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is something else going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:16.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:22.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what happens when amateurs\Ntry to do a professional's job!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:25.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I {\i1}have{\i0} been overthinking this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.22,0:15:33.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't tell them you were the great\NKogoro Mouri's daughter, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.81,0:15:35.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.90,0:15:37.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:41.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope this taught you not to go sticking\Nyour neck into other people's business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.85,0:15:45.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:46.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.79,0:15:57.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I guess I just can't compete with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.30,0:16:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.37,0:16:12.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, I don't think you\Nmade a mistake in your reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.52,0:16:20.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, I overheard the salesmen\Nat the place they sell sports cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:25.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is going to buy a sports\Ncar that costs ¥25,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.85,0:16:28.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,¥25,000,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:29.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's he getting the money from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.74,0:16:33.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s insurance policy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he {\i1}is{\i0} trying to kill Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:41.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after he pays off the loan on the\Nhouse, he'll still have ¥60,000,000 left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.06,0:16:46.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was no sign that the air\Nin the house was contaminated...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.22,0:16:48.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was poisoning her food?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.32,0:16:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I think she does all the cooking...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:54.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.88,0:17:04.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.65,0:17:05.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is he doing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.54,0:17:12.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While I'm sitting here, danger\Ncould be creeping up on Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.22,0:17:15.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Shin'ichi, what am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.90,0:17:18.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Something's bugging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.03,0:17:22.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And it's been bugging me\Never since Ran told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.48,0:17:26.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is it, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.56,0:17:28.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.05,0:17:29.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Didn't Chie{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} say...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:32.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it! I've figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.75,0:17:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to know what\NChie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.17,0:17:40.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. What did she say about her dizzy spells?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.21,0:17:43.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall correctly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.42,0:17:50.95,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's probably the weather.\NThe temperature's been all over the place lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.95,0:17:54.11,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And I guess the fatigue's been building up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.11,0:17:55.62,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}since I have to drive to and\Nfrom Shizuoka every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.65,0:18:01.09,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As proof, when there's no school,\Nor when it's cool, even on a weekday,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.09,0:18:03.09,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I feel fine—nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.46,0:18:06.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.10,0:18:09.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it were something in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.84,0:18:12.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then wouldn't the symptoms\Nbe worse on her days off,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:17.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when she's at home longer,\Ninstead of when she's out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:19.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.98,0:18:24.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the thing that's giving her headaches\Nand dizzy spells isn't in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.15,0:18:26.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.58,0:18:29.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, at the design school in Shizuoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:32.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someplace between her house and the school...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.68,0:18:37.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.12,0:18:43.24,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The next morning
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:43.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going for my walk now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.28,0:18:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is ham and eggs for breakfast okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:47.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.15,0:18:50.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be hungry when I get home, so make a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.35,0:19:36.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:38.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:40.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just put in your pocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:44.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an air conditioner disinfectant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.40,0:19:45.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.46,0:19:47.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to protect Chie from\Ncold germs and other bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:52.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then when the police get here,\Nyou'll show that to them, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.56,0:19:57.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just called them. I have a friend on the force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.16,0:20:00.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Police?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.91,0:20:06.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would never have dreamed that her husband, the man she trusted most,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.65,0:20:12.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was spraying an "invisible weapon" into\Nher car's air conditioner every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:16.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never got sick\Nwhen she didn't drive to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.10,0:20:20.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or when it was cool enough that she\Ndidn't have to use the air conditioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:27.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:31.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.03,0:20:51.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Later, the police investigation\Nshowed that the spray bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:53.98,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}contained a dilluted organic chlorine solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.21,0:21:00.64,Narration Off,,0010,0010,0000,,{\be10}Akio Yoshino had embezzled several million yen from his company, and was trying to cover the loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.64,0:21:04.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But he also wanted a new sports car,\Nand that's why he thought up this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.68,0:21:05.90,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's what his confession stated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.23,0:22:46.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sold the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.80,0:22:49.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And along with some\Nfriends and flower shops,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.80,0:22:52.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she opened her own flower design company!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:52.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.33,0:22:54.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.06,0:22:56.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's looking great!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.00,0:22:59.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chie Taniguchi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.74,0:23:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She got a divorce and went\Nback to her maiden name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.18,0:23:05.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez. Women get over things so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.50,0:23:09.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But Ran sure was sharp, getting\Nsuspicious about Akio Yoshino
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.23,0:23:10.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}over a little thing like a bump on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.15,0:23:13.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure glad things worked out for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.15,0:23:17.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't noticed anything and done what\Nyou did, Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might be dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:21.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're getting to be like you-know-who?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.00,0:23:24.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.47,0:23:28.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess you could say I wanted\Nto understand him a little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:31.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe get to feel closer to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.37,0:23:35.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:40.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So do you understand\NShin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} a little more now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.56,0:23:44.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.43,0:23:47.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who can understand that mystery geek?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.89,0:23:50.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.27,0:23:53.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But never mind that.\NLet's go eat some cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.85,0:23:54.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.60,0:23:58.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, I guess it's for the best...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.56,0:24:06.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he trying to damage his own car?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.84,0:24:15.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, doesn't the president\Nhave a cell phone with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.51,0:24:19.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.69,0:24:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.10,0:24:24.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.54,0:24:30.63,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.63,0:24:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Open Window
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.35,0:24:36.95,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time...
